text: St. Mary of Eton is an Anglican church at Hackney Wick, London and a Grade II listed building. It was built 1890–92 in the medieval Gothic style. It is notable as the founding location of 59 Club, where its ample parking, large hall with table tennis, billiards, a juke box and a coffee bar provided meeting place once a week on Saturday evenings.
